{{orphan|date=March 2017}} '''Janet Allard''' is an American playwright and theatre educator who was born and raised in Hawaii. She currently teaches in the Theatre Department at the [[University of North Carolina at Greensboro]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vpa.uncg.edu/bios/janet-allard|title=Faculty {{!}} UNCG College of Visual and Performing Arts|website=vpa.uncg.edu|language=en|access-date=2017-03-04}}</ref> Allard's plays have been produced at The Guthrie Lab, The Kennedy Center, Mixed Blood Theatre Company, [[Playwrights Horizons]], [[Yale Repertory Theatre]], The Yale Cabaret, The Women's Project and Productions, Perseverance Theatre, The House Of Candles, and Access Theater in New York City, as well as internationally in Ireland, England, Greece, and New Zealand. She has twice been awarded a Jerome Fellowship by [[The Playwrights' Center]] in Minneapolis and has been a [[MacDowell Colony]] Fellow and a [[Fulbright Program|Fulbright]] Fellow (1998, New Zealand and the South Pacific).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.playscripts.com/playwrights/bios/124|title=Janet Allard {{!}} Playscripts, Inc.|website=www.playscripts.com|language=en|access-date=2017-03-04}}</ref>
Her plays and productions include ''Pool Boy'', which premiered at Barrington Stage Company in 2010;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://berkshireonstage.com/2010/07/22/frisky-pool-boy-tries-hard-to-please-at-barrington-stage/|title=Frisky "Pool Boy" tries hard to please at Barrington Stage|last=Says|first=Dain62|date=2010-07-22|website=BERKSHIRE ON STAGE and SCREEN|access-date=2017-03-04}}</ref> ''Vrooommm!'', which premiered at the Summer Play Festival in New York City in 2007<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2016-03-12|title=Summer Play Festival|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Summer_Play_Festival&oldid=709698516|journal=Wikipedia|language=en}}</ref> and was later produced by Triad Stage in Winston-Salem, NC in 2016;<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.journalnow.com/relishnow/the_arts/performing_arts/on-and-off-the-track-the-action-is-constant-in/article_2dd4e4cf-ade9-584a-a71d-d9b84a09c985.html|title=On and off the track, the action is constant in Triad Stage’s "Vrooommm!"|last=Correspondent|first=BILL CISSNA Special|work=Winston-Salem Journal|access-date=2017-03-04|language=en}}</ref> and ''Privates'' in ''Bill of (W)Rights'' at Mixed Blood Theatre in 2004.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.minnesota.publicradio.org/features/2004/02/25_combsm_mixedblood/|title=MPR: Walking around a theater to learn about the "Bill of (W)rights"|last=Radio|first=Minnesota Public|website=news.minnesota.publicradio.org|language=en|access-date=2017-03-04}}</ref> ''The Unknown: a silent musical'' was developed with P73 Productions, garnered an award from the Jonathan Larson Foundation, and was presented at Joe's Pub and the New York Musical Theater Festival in 2005.
